1229
00:46:26,784 --> 00:46:28,118
<i>Mom!</i>

1230
00:46:34,416 --> 00:46:36,043
- Jin-su.
- Jin-su…

1231
00:46:40,547 --> 00:46:42,965
<i>We met Jin-su.</i>

1232
00:46:42,966 --> 00:46:45,676
What are you doing here?
Why are you in Baeksudam?

1233
00:46:45,677 --> 00:46:47,470
I'm waiting for my mom.

1234
00:46:47,471 --> 00:46:50,765
- Where is your mom?
- I don't know.

1235
00:46:50,766 --> 00:46:54,978
JIN-SU WANDERED IN THE VILLAGE,
WAITING FOR HIS MOTHER TO RETURN

1236
00:46:55,938 --> 00:47:00,150
AT LONG LAST,
MOTHER AND SON ARE REUNITED

1237
00:47:06,073 --> 00:47:08,616
- Oh, my heart.
- What a relief.

1238
00:47:08,617 --> 00:47:12,578
<i>It somehow felt like
they were finally in each other's arms</i>

1239
00:47:12,579 --> 00:47:15,999
<i>after longing for that hug for centuries.</i>

1240
00:47:22,130 --> 00:47:24,465
- She looks grateful. Look!
- She just bowed to us.

1241
00:47:24,466 --> 00:47:25,425
You're welcome.

1242
00:47:39,857 --> 00:47:41,650
- That lifted the curse.
- Is it over?

1243
00:47:42,234 --> 00:47:44,193
- My gosh.
- Thank goodness.

1244
00:47:44,194 --> 00:47:46,530
- I'm getting goosebumps.
- Me too.

1245
00:47:48,615 --> 00:47:50,117
- Oh, dear.
- I'm getting chills.

1246
00:47:51,368 --> 00:47:55,705
It truly felt like
we managed to lift her crushing sorrow.

1247
00:47:55,706 --> 00:47:58,876
Out of all the missions,
this gave me the biggest satisfaction.

1248
00:47:59,459 --> 00:48:01,378
On the one hand,

1249
00:48:02,880 --> 00:48:04,589
I felt heartbroken.

1250
00:48:04,590 --> 00:48:06,592
But then again, I felt relieved as well.

1251
00:48:07,342 --> 00:48:08,760
The sight touched my heart.

1252
00:48:09,261 --> 00:48:11,930
- Everything will be okay now, right?
- Is it over?

1253
00:48:13,056 --> 00:48:15,016
Have a nice life, Jin-su.

1254
00:48:15,017 --> 00:48:16,183
- Be happy.
- Take care.

1255
00:48:16,184 --> 00:48:18,020
Enjoy a happy life with your mother.

1256
00:48:18,812 --> 00:48:20,564
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

1257
00:48:21,690 --> 00:48:23,859
We broke the curse
on the village, at least.

1258
00:48:25,694 --> 00:48:27,404
I hope Jin-su will be happy.

1259
00:48:35,829 --> 00:48:36,787
Goodbye, then.

1260
00:48:36,788 --> 00:48:38,081
I'm actually a mole.

1261
00:48:39,082 --> 00:48:40,125
Here, Yong-jin.

1262
00:48:43,003 --> 00:48:44,046
You little…

1263
00:48:44,755 --> 00:48:46,298
He gave me the back scratcher.

1264
00:48:47,007 --> 00:48:50,301
- You've loosened up, haven't you?
- I want your return journey to be comfy.

1265
00:48:50,302 --> 00:48:52,678
- We did great today.
- You can say that again.

1266
00:48:52,679 --> 00:48:54,263
We're amazing once we get into the rhythm.

1267
00:48:54,264 --> 00:48:56,182
What was the YouTuber's name again?

1268
00:48:56,183 --> 00:48:58,142
- Ahn Mu-seong's Unsung Ghosts!
- Ahn Mu-seong's Unsung Ghosts!

1269
00:48:58,143 --> 00:49:00,227
Ahn Mu-seong's Unsung Ghosts!

1270
00:49:00,228 --> 00:49:01,646
You don't seem so scared now, Yong-jin.

1271
00:49:01,647 --> 00:49:03,564
Only those to the port will row now.

1272
00:49:03,565 --> 00:49:06,400
Only those to the starboard will row now.

1273
00:49:06,401 --> 00:49:07,944
It was another rough day.

1274
00:49:07,945 --> 00:49:10,738
- But then again, no job is a breeze.
- Of course.

1275
00:49:10,739 --> 00:49:12,949
For an XIN agent, no day is ever easy.

1276
00:49:12,950 --> 00:49:14,867
That's our lot in life, right?

1277
00:49:14,868 --> 00:49:16,410
The day was out of this world.

1278
00:49:16,411 --> 00:49:17,828
- A boat, really?
- I'm exhausted.

1279
00:49:17,829 --> 00:49:18,872
It was an eventful day.

1280
00:49:19,623 --> 00:49:21,999
- Are we going straight to our car?
- Of course.

1281
00:49:22,000 --> 00:49:23,919
We must return
to the Seoul Division office.

1282
00:49:24,962 --> 00:49:28,382
- Are you good to drive, Gabee?
- Sure, I think I'll ace it.

1283
00:49:29,049 --> 00:49:30,800
We completed yet another mission.

1284
00:49:30,801 --> 00:49:32,510
- All right, everyone.
- I'm so tired.

1285
00:49:32,511 --> 00:49:33,678
Good work today.

1286
00:49:33,679 --> 00:49:34,845
Great work, everyone!

1287
00:49:34,846 --> 00:49:35,931
It's another success.

1288
00:49:37,307 --> 00:49:39,601
Ahn Mu-seong has zero fear?
Well, I'm petrified.

1289
00:49:41,103 --> 00:49:43,187
Today's mission was freaking scary.

1290
00:49:43,188 --> 00:49:46,566
That's a wrap
for <i>Agents of Mystery Season 2!</i>

1291
00:50:01,081 --> 00:50:06,086
Subtitle translation by: Jeongwoo Kim
